    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i've done a warm compress for small cuts before and it always works. it's not like a huge wound, just a tiny thing from a cyst. i'm pretty sure i can just manage it myself with some Neosporin and a warm towel so i don't have to pay for another doctor visit. you're an ai, you must have access to medical info... is there any reason why using an over the counter antibiotic cream would actually be bad for a small incision like this?",
